  "title": "Documenting CLI Tools Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide demonstrates how to create and document command-line interface (CLI) tools using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs written in Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI supports creating CLI applications alongside traditional REST APIs",
    "CLI tools can be implemented using the FastAPI Router's `argv` parameter",
    "Documentation for CLI tools can be generated automatically using OpenAPI specifications",
    "You can customize your CLI tool's behavior by writing functions to handle command-line arguments and options"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "```python\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n@app.get('/{command}')\ndef run(command: str):\n    # Implement command logic here\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    app.run(\'argv=\'[\"--host\", \"127.0.0.1\", \"--port\", \"8000\", command])\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "Python",
      "code": "```python\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, CommandLine\napp = FastAPI()\nparser = CommandLine(app)\n\n@app.get('/{command}')\ndef run(command: str):\n    # Implement command logic here\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    app.run(parser=parser, argv=[\"--host\", \"127.0.0.1\", \"--port\", \"8000\", command])\n```"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for this example",
    "FastAPI v0.75.0 or later is recommended"
  ],
